footnotes.text: Unless otherwise specified, screening procedures should be done within 21 days prior to randomization.
footnotes.classificationReasoning: Specifies timing window (21 days prior) for screening procedures, affecting visit scheduling.
Specifies that informed consent must occur before screening procedures, affecting sequence.

footnotes.text: Medications (prescription or over-the-counter, including vitamins and herbal supplements) will be documented beginning with the Screening Visit and continuing until 30 days following the last dose of study treatment. Serious and non-serious adverse events occurring after the study-specific informed consent is signed but prior to the initial dose of venetoclax/placebo, bortezomib or dexamethasone will be collected only if they are considered by the Investigator to be causally related to the study-required procedures.
footnotes.classificationReasoning: Describes data collection procedures and documentation requirements without creating conditional logic.

footnotes.text: Full physical examination done at screening, including height and weight.
footnotes.classificationReasoning: Specifies what to include in physical examination, operational instruction without conditional logic.
Creates conditional branch logic based on country subset (Japan and France only).
Creates conditional branch logic based on country subset (France only).

footnotes.text: Labs may be performed within 21 days prior to randomization unless otherwise noted. Historical panels may be used if done within 21 days prior to randomization. Additional labs may be performed as clinically necessary. Refer to Section 5.3.1.1.1 for details on specific testing required for each panel.
footnotes.classificationReasoning: Multi-label: Specifies timing window (21 days) for labs AND provides operational instructions about historical panels and clinical necessity.

footnotes.text: Serum pregnancy test within 21 days prior to randomization for women of childbearing potential. Will be completed per certified local laboratory.
footnotes.classificationReasoning: Multi-label: Creates conditional branch (women of childbearing potential) AND specifies timing window (21 days prior).

footnotes.text: Must include complete blood count (CBC), differential, and platelets. Must be done within 2 weeks prior to randomization. Will be completed per certified local laboratory.
footnotes.classificationReasoning: Multi-label: Specifies timing constraint (2 weeks prior) AND operational details about what to include in test.

footnotes.text: Skeletal survey consists of lateral radiograph of skull, anteroposterior and lateral views of spine, and antero-posterior views of pelvis, ribs, femora, tibiae, fibulae, humeri, ulnae and radii. Historical results obtained within 30 days prior to randomization may be used at Screening provided that the images meet the requirements in the Image Acquisition Guidelines. Use of conventional or low dose CT scan, or MRI bone survey is acceptable.
footnotes.classificationReasoning: Multi-label: Describes operational details about skeletal survey AND allows historical results within 30 days (timing constraint).
Creates conditional branch logic based on country subset (Japan only).

footnotes.text: CT, PET/CT or MRI (same method should be used throughout study) should be performed in all subjects with a history of plasmacytomas or if clinically indicated at baseline to assess for the presence of extramedullary plasmacytoma.
footnotes.classificationReasoning: Creates conditional branch based on clinical history (plasmacytomas) or clinical indication.

footnotes.text: Once all screening procedures have been performed and eligibility has been confirmed, subject can be randomized. The first dose of study treatment must be administered within 5 days of date of randomization.
footnotes.classificationReasoning: Specifies timing constraint that first dose must occur within 5 days of randomization.
